The evidence with the title 'L.A. County homelessness jumps a 'staggering' 23% as need far ... ' says May 31, 2017  ... Mirroring last year 's count, only one of every four homeless people in both the city and across the county were classified as “ sheltered, ” meaning they were counted in an emergency shelter or longer-term transitional program. That left three of every four, or just under 43,000 countywide, living on the street. 
